### Usage

{{#usage-guide}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Initialize the Square Payments object

Initialize the Square [Payments](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/Payments) object with your application ID and the ID of the seller location where the payment is taken.

```javascript
const payments = Square.payments(APPLICATION_ID, LOCATION_ID);
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Create an ACH object

Get a new [ACH](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/ACH) instance with all of the behaviors
and properties needed to take the payment.

```javascript
const ach = await payments.ach();
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Get the one-time payment token from the ACH object

Get the payment token from the [ACH](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/ACH) object when the
buyer completes the form. Calling ach.tokenize will trigger a
modal whereby the buyer will be able to select their bank account.
The [tokenize](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/ACH#ACH.tokenize) method accepts the account holder's name as a required argument.

```javascript
this.elements.token.value = await ach.tokenize({
  accountHolderName: 'John Doe',
});
```

If the buyer's bank information is valid, `ach.tokenize()` will return a one-time
use token to make a call to the Payments API [CreatePayment](https://developer.squareup.com/reference/square/payments-api/create-payment) endpoint to charge a customer. Otherwise, it will return an
error you can present to the customer.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{/usage-guide}}

### Usage

{{#usage-guide}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Initialize the Square payments object

Initialize the Square [Payments](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/Payments) object with your application ID and the ID of the seller location where the payment is taken.

```javascript
const payments = Square.payments(APPLICATION_ID, LOCATION_ID);
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Get a new Card object

```javascript
const card = await payments.card();
```

This creates a new [Card](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/Card) instance with all of the behaviors
and properties needed to take a card payment.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Attach the Card instance to a DOM element

Attach the [Card](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/Card) instance to an empty DOM element
on your page. The payment card form renders into the
empty element, turning it into a secure payment card form.

```javascript
await card.attach('#card');
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Get the payment token

Get the payment form token from the [Card](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/Card) instance when the
buyer completes the form by calling the [tokenize](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/Card#Card.tokenize) method.

```javascript
const tokenResult = await card.tokenize();
if (tokenResult.status === 'OK') {
  const token = tokenResult.token;
} else {
  console.error(tokenResult.errors);
}
```

If the payment card information is valid, it returns a one-time-use
token which you can use to create a Payment using the Payments API [CreatePayment](https://developer.squareup.com/reference/square/payments-api/create-payment) endpoint to charge a customer. Otherwise, it will return an
error that you can present to the customer.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{/usage-guide}}

### Usage

{{#usage-guide}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Initialize the Square Payments object

Initialize the Square [Payments](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/Payments) object with your application ID and the ID of the seller location where the payment is taken.

```javascript
const payments = Square.payments(APPLICATION_ID, LOCATION_ID);
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Create a GiftCard object

```javascript
const giftCard = await payments.giftCard();
```

This creates a new [GiftCard](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/GiftCard) instance with all of the behaviors
and properties needed to take a Gift Card payment.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Attach the GiftCard object to your page

Attach the [GiftCard](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/GiftCard) object to an empty DOM element
on your page. The Gift Card form renders into the
empty element, turning it into a secure gift card form.

```javascript
await giftCard.attach('#gift-card');
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Get the one-time payment token from the GiftCard object

Get the payment token from the `GiftCard` object when the
buyer completes the form by calling the [tokenize](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/GiftCard#GiftCard.tokenize) method.

```javascript
this.elements.token.value = await giftCard.tokenize();
```

If the Gift Card information is valid, it returns a one-time
use token to make a call to the Payments API [CreatePayment](https://developer.squareup.com/reference/square/payments-api/create-payment) endpoint to charge a customer. Otherwise, it will return an
error that you can present to the customer.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{/usage-guide}}

### Quick Setup

{{#usage-guide}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Initialize the SDK

Add the following script to the `<head>` of your index.html page, this will setup the SDK in testing a sanbox enviroment. Remove sandbox. from the URL when developing for production.

```javascript
<script src="https://sandbox.web.squarecdn.com/v1/square.js"></script>
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Choose a payment method

The [Payments](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/Payments) object provides factory methods for the payment methods. To complete a payment scenario, see one of the following payment methods:

- [Card Payments](/reference/sdks/web/payments/card-payments)
- [ACH Payments](/reference/sdks/web/payments/bank-payments)
- [Apple Pay](/reference/sdks/web/payments/digital-wallets/apple-pay)
- [Google Pay](/reference/sdks/web/payments/digital-wallets/google-pay)
- [Square Gift Card](/reference/sdks/web/payments/gift-cards)

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{/usage-guide}}

