#### Create a PaymentRequest with the total amount

Create a new [PaymentRequest](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/PaymentRequest) using the
desired options. At the minimum, you need to provide the total amount,
the countryCode, and the currencyCode. **Note:** The amount
field is formatted for display, including decimal places. When creating a payment
with the [Payments API](https://developer.squareup.com/reference/square/payments-api/create-payment), the amount must be formatted as the payment amount in the
smallest unit of currency. For example, $5.79 would be 579 cents.

```javascript
const request = payments.paymentRequest({
  countryCode: 'US',
  currencyCode: 'USD',
  total: { amount: '5.79', label: 'Total' },
});
```

The [PaymentRequest](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/PaymentRequest) is created by
the SDK with payment request options that your application
provides in a [paymentRequestOptions](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/PaymentRequestOptions)
object that you declare.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Create an ApplePay object

Get a new ApplePay object with your [PaymentRequest](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/PaymentRequest).

```javascript
const applePay = await payments.applePay(request);
```

This creates a new [ApplePay](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/ApplePay) instance with all of the behaviors and properties needed to take an Apple Pay payment.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Get the one-time payment token from the ApplePay object

Get the payment token from the [ApplePay](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/ApplePay) object when the
buyer completes the form by calling the [tokenize](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/ApplePay#ApplePay.tokenize) method.

```javascript
const tokenResult = await applePay.tokenize();
if (tokenResult.status === 'OK') {
  const token = tokenResult.token;
} else {
  console.error(tokenResult.errors);
}
```

If the Apple Pay information is valid, the tokenResult will include an `'OK'`,
status as well as a one-time-use token which can be used to make a call to the Payments API [CreatePayment](https://developer.squareup.com/reference/square/payments-api/create-payment) endpoint to charge a customer.
If the Apple Pay information is not valid, it will return an error that you can present to the customer.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
