### Usage

{{#usage-guide}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Initialize the Square Payments object

Initialize the Square [Payments](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/Payments) object with your application ID and the ID of the seller location where the payment is taken.

```javascript
const payments = Square.payments(APPLICATION_ID, LOCATION_ID);
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Create a PaymentRequest with the total amount

Create a new [PaymentRequest](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/PaymentRequest) using the
desired options. At the minimum, you need to provide the total amount,
the countryCode, and the currencyCode. **Note:** The amount
field is formatted for display, including decimal places. When creating a payment
with the [Payments API](https://developer.squareup.com/reference/square/payments-api/create-payment), the amount must be formatted as the payment amount in the
smallest unit of currency. For example, $5.79 would be 579 cents.

```javascript
const request = payments.paymentRequest({
  countryCode: 'US',
  currencyCode: 'USD',
  total: {
    amount: '5.79',
    label: 'Total',
  },
});
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Create a GooglePay instance

Create a new `GooglePay` instance using your [PaymentRequest](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/PaymentRequest).

```javascript
const googlePay = await payments.googlePay(request);
```

This creates a new [GooglePay](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/GooglePay) instance with all of the behaviors
and properties needed to take a Google Pay payment.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Attach the GooglePay instance to the page

Attach the `GooglePay` instance to an empty DOM element on your page. The Google Pay
button renders into the empty element. You can also specify a number of
[options](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/GooglePayButtonOptions) that determine the look of the button itself such as the button color, and the
button type.

```javascript
googlePay.attach('#googlePay', { buttonColor: 'default', buttonType: 'long' });
```

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{#usage-guide-step}}

#### Trigger the Google Pay payment sheet and receive a payment token

Trigger the Google Pay payment sheet and receive a payment token from the [GooglePay](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/GooglePay)
instance when the buyer completes their interaction by calling the
[tokenize](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/GooglePay#GooglePay.tokenize) method. This method returns a promise which resolves with a [TokenResult](/reference/sdks/web/payments/objects/TokenResult).

```javascript
const tokenResult = await googlePay.tokenize();
if (tokenResult.status === 'OK') {
  const token = tokenResult.token;
} else {
  console.error(tokenResult.errors);
}
```

If the Google Pay information is valid, the tokenResult will include an `'OK'`,
status as well as a one-time-use token which can be used as the `source_id` when making a call to the Payments API [CreatePayment](https://developer.squareup.com/reference/square/payments-api/create-payment) endpoint to charge a customer.
If the Google Pay information is not valid, it will return an error that you can present to the customer.

{{/usage-guide-step}}
{{/usage-guide}}
